<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="181" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1407,1610]" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,235,1407,1429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">Diagnosis</emphasis>
:—This new species can be distinguished from its morphologically closest relative, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Philcox" authorityYear="1992" box="[1033,1123,1408,1429]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Cryptanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruthae">
<emphasis box="[1033,1123,1408,1429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">C. ruthae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by its caulescent habit, 
<quantity box="[1357,1451,1408,1429]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" unit="cm" value="25.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="20.0">20–30 cm</quantity>
long (
<emphasis box="[247,267,1444,1465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">vs</emphasis>
. stemless), shorter leaf blades (
<quantity box="[572,669,1444,1465]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" unit="cm" value="27.0" valueMax="32.0" valueMin="22.0">22–32 cm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[676,696,1444,1465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">vs</emphasis>
. to 
<emphasis box="[734,763,1444,1465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">ca.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[769,829,1444,1466]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" unit="cm" value="65.0">65 cm</quantity>
long), with margins equally densely spinulose (
<emphasis box="[1295,1321,1444,1465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">vs.</emphasis>
entire except for its serrate distal end), shorter sepals (
<emphasis box="[575,605,1480,1501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">ca.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[609,675,1480,1501]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[681,701,1480,1501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[712,819,1480,1501]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" unit="mm" value="18.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="17.0">17–20 mm</quantity>
), which are shorter connate at the base (for 
<quantity box="[1231,1310,1480,1502]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[1315,1335,1480,1501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[1347,1441,1480,1501]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="8.0">8–12 mm</quantity>
), and narrower sepal lobes (
<emphasis box="[443,466,1516,1537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">ca</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[477,550,1516,1538]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[557,577,1516,1537]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">vs</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[589,668,1516,1537]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
wide).
</paragraph>
